House Bill 138
By: Representatives Neal of the 79th, Crowe of the 118th, and Hitchens of the 161st
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 35-8-7 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the
2 powers and duties of the Georgia Peace Officer Standards and Training Council, so as
3 establish basic and in-service training courses on de-escalation techniques and methods; to
4 provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Code Section 35-8-7 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to the powers and
8 duties of the Georgia Peace Officer Standards and Training Council, is amended by revising
9 paragraph (20) as follows:
10 "(20) To establish as part of the curriculum for basic and in-service training courses for
11 all peace officers training on organized criminal activity, and criminal street gangs, and
12 de-escalation techniques and methods that include scenario based training;"
13 SECTION 2.
14 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
